//Synchronous function
// compiler will execute line by line
// example:-Waiting for an action to complete then after go for another action

//Asynchronous function
// compiler will execute line by line untill the command takes time to get executed 
// example:- at the time of waiting for a command to execute another command will executed to save time
// async function has promise that returns the status of all the tasks seted up.
// async funtion has an await keyword that indicates that the compiler has to wait for the promise untill the awaited tasks are not completed


// solcjs converts from a high-level solidity language into Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) bytecode so that it can be executed on the blockchain by EVM.